---
layout: base.njk
pageTitle: "CCSU LLB Previous Year Papers 2016-2025 | AI Exam Prep | Last Minute Law"
pageDescription: "AI-analyzed CCSU LLB previous year question papers (2016-2025). Smart predictions, scoring strategies, syllabus, case laws & exam tips for all 6 semesters. Free for CCS University law students."
---

<section class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="hero-split">
      <div>
        <div class="hero-kicker fade-in">CCSU LLB · Semester IV · 2016–2025</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title fade-in d1">Know exactly<br>what to study.</h1>
        <p class="hero-deck fade-in d2">Every previous year question — analyzed by AI. Probability scores, safe scoring combos, golden case laws — all free, forever.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions fade-in d2">
          <a href="#subjects" class="btn-solid">See the Analysis →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SUBJECTS — Static HTML for SEO -->
<section id="subjects">
  <header class="section-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head-inner">
        <div>
          <div class="section-kicker">Semester IV</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">The Papers, Decoded.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="section-deck">AI-Analyzed Question Bank · {{ subjects | length }} subjects</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="subject-grid">
      {%- for slug, s in subjects %}
      <a href="/{{ slug }}/" class="subject-card">
        <div class="sc-top">
          <span class="sc-code mono">{{ s.code }}</span>
          <div class="sc-badges">
            {%- if s.optional %}<span class="chip">Optional</span>{%- endif %}
            {%- if s.practical %}<span class="chip chip--green">Practical</span>{%- endif %}
          </div>
        </div>
        <h3 class="sc-name">{{ s.name }}</h3>
        <p class="sc-desc">{{ s.oneLiner }}</p>
        <div class="sc-pills">
          <span class="sc-pill">{{ s.difficulty }}</span>
          <span class="sc-pill">{{ s.style }}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sc-footer">
          <span></span>
          <span class="sc-footer-right">Read <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></span>
        </div>
      </a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TIPS — Static SEO content -->
<section id="tips">
  <header class="section-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head-inner">
        <div>
          <div class="section-kicker">Playbook</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Tips &amp; Guidelines</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="tips-grid">
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num mono">01</div>
        <h3 class="tip-title">Section C First</h3>
        <p>Start your paper with Section C (3×20 = 60 marks). These long answers carry the most weight. Pick the 3 you know best and write comprehensive answers with case laws, sections, and headings.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num mono">02</div>
        <h3 class="tip-title">Passing Marks Strategy</h3>
        <p>You need 36/100 to pass. Section A alone is 20 marks. Get Section A right + answer 1 Section C properly (20 marks) = 40 marks. That's your safety net even on a bad day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num mono">03</div>
        <h3 class="tip-title">Case Laws Win Marks</h3>
        <p>Citing relevant case laws in Section C bumps your answer from average to excellent. You don't need to remember full citations — just the case name, year, and the principle established.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num mono">04</div>
        <h3 class="tip-title">Repeat Topics = Free Marks</h3>
        <p>Some topics repeat in 80-100% of papers. These are your guaranteed questions. Master the top 5 priorities in each subject and you'll recognise at least 3 Section C questions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num mono">05</div>
        <h3 class="tip-title">Word Limits Matter</h3>
        <p>Section A: 50-75 words max. Section B: 150-200 words. Section C: 400-500 words minimum. Examiners check length — a short Section C answer will not get full marks regardless of quality.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-card">
        <div class="tip-num mono">06</div>
        <h3 class="tip-title">Time Management</h3>
        <p>3-hour paper. Spend: Section C = 90 min (30 min each), Section B = 40 min (20 min each), Section A = 30 min (6 min each), Review = 10 min. Never leave Section C incomplete.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ — Schema.org FAQPage for rich snippets -->
<section id="faq">
  <header class="section-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head-inner">
        <div>
          <div class="section-kicker">Common Questions</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">FAQ</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary><h3>What is the passing mark for CCSU LLB?</h3></summary>
        <p>36 out of 100 (36%) per paper is required to pass each CCSU LLB subject. Total 500 marks per semester across 5 papers.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary><h3>Can I fail papers and still pass CCSU LLB semester?</h3></summary>
        <p>Yes. If you fail 1 or 2 papers, you are promoted to the next semester and must clear them as back papers. Failing 3 or more papers results in semester back — you must repeat the whole semester.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary><h3>What is the CCSU LLB exam pattern?</h3></summary>
        <p>Each 3-hour paper has 100 marks split as: Section A (5 compulsory × 4 marks = 20), Section B (2 of 3 × 10 marks = 20), Section C (3 of 5 × 20 marks = 60).</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary><h3>Which optional subject should I choose in CCSU LLB Semester 4?</h3></summary>
        <p>Banking Law (K-4006) is most commonly offered and easier for definition-based scoring. Criminology (K-4004) is best for essay writers. Law of Trust (K-4005) is rarely offered at most colleges.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

